From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Crow Maintainers <crow@localhost>
Date: Thu, 1 Jan 1970 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/6] Disable electron-updater for Crow-pinned AppImage builds

Crow ships the pet-mode AppImage from a specific pinned upstream SHA
(see .gitmodules for `vendor/open-llm-vtuber-web`). Upstream's
electron-updater machinery expects to phone home to a GitHub release
channel that Crow does not publish to — leaving it enabled would either
fail silently on first launch or, worse, pull a newer upstream with
patches unapplied. We strip the autoUpdater wiring and replace it with
an in-process no-op so the rest of the app behaves identically.

Applies against: vendor/open-llm-vtuber-web @ d176e7df2366952e3bacbf12cf9a8b18a4315932

TODO(Phase 3.1): fill in hunks once the submodule is checked out and
line numbers are stable. Touch points already surveyed:
- package.json   — remove `electron-updater` dep line
- src/main/index.ts — drop any autoUpdater import / init call (none at
  d176e7d; this patch may be a no-op on the current pin, in which case
  keep the patch file as a guardrail for future SHA bumps)
- electron-builder.yml — ensure `publish` is `null` (currently unset,
  which defaults to GitHub; make explicit)
